{
  "text": "Next, we examined cyclization of the AC253 peptide for its antagonist activity at AMY3 and whether it also retained its neuroprotective properties against Ab toxicity using two in vitro functional bioassays. Amylin receptors are heterodimers of CTR and one of three RAMPs (RAMP1, 2, and 3), thus generating multiple amylin receptor subtypes, AMY1, AMY2, and AMY3 [CITATION_1] . Our previous data provide evidence that the AMY3 is the most relevant subtype of amylin receptors in the context of the direct actions of Ab (and hAmylin) at the level of the cell membrane [CITATION_2] , and we thus targeted this receptor isoform in the present study.",
